Commentary: shorter length, 130kph, he jabs it off the inside edge onto pad and it rolls away for a single

139kph, full down leg and he glances this fine! Marsh rolling now. Easy pickings
139kph, back of a length, angled across, he late cuts neatly straight to backward square
121kph, short slower ball, he rolls the wrists on a pull shot to the man at backward square

fuller on leg, he pushes this to mid on

leg break on middle, he drives back to the bowler who knocks it down

driven firmly to long on
full on leg, he clips this along the ground to deep midwicket

back of a length on off, he defends from the crease to point
134kph, short on the hip, he pulls behind square! Nicely done, swivelling on the short length
play and miss, he tries to late cut and misses. It was too tight
full on leg, he drives firmly to long on
looped up outside of, he gets taken on the pad
looped way wide of off and called a wide
full on middle, he drives to long on

Is he stumped? Lenton thinks so. The TV umpire is called for. Slower and higher outside off, he misses a sweep and Lenton takes the bails off. Has Bowe bowled a no-ball though? Just got part of the heel behind the line. Harris had the foot out of the crease when Lenton whipped the bails off. That is out. He dragged his foot out trying to sweep. Nice work from Lenton
